div.p:
VII. Shall you not prevent a multitude of sins, if you make hast in your Younger Yeats to come to God? whereas if you go on in your Sins, what a Multitude of sins, how many Thousand sins will you add more and more to the sins that you have already committed; 
                  •
               f you loiter still, how many Prayers will you neglect; And how many Sabbaths prophane? And how many lies tell, and make no Conscience? And how many Oaths may some of you swear? Whereas, now if you would come to God in your Youth, if you would now Believe and Repent, and come to God, O what a number of Sins may you prevent the commission of! And is not this desirable? You have sinned enough already, the Youngest amongst you have sinned enough already, you need not go on still, and add more and more to your sins; for they are not to be numbred already
